    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Indexed computation: (start-state end-state value)
; Compose only when indices match: T(i,j) ; T(j,k) = T(i,k)

(define (make-indexed start end val) (list start end val))
(define idx-start car)
(define idx-end cadr)
(define idx-val caddr)

(define (idx-bind m f)
  (let* ((j (idx-end m))
         (result (f (idx-val m))))
    (if (eq? j (idx-start result))
        (make-indexed (idx-start m) (idx-end result) (idx-val result))
        (begin (display "ERROR: Index mismatch — handshake failed") (newline)))))

; raw -> filtered -> ranked
(define step1 (make-indexed 'raw 'filtered '(a b c)))
(define step2-fn (lambda (v) (make-indexed 'filtered 'ranked (length v))))

(define pipeline (idx-bind step1 step2-fn))
(display "pipeline: ") (display pipeline) (newline)
; (raw ranked 3) — indices chain, handshake holds
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Indexed computation in Python
class Indexed:
    def __init__(self, start, end, val):
        self.start, self.end, self.val = start, end, val

    def bind(self, f):
        result = f(self.val)
        assert self.end == result.start, f"Index mismatch: {self.end} != {result.start}"
        return Indexed(self.start, result.end, result.val)

    def __repr__(self):
        return f"({self.start} -> {self.end}: {self.val})"

step1 = Indexed("raw", "filtered", ["a", "b", "c"])
step2 = lambda v: Indexed("filtered", "ranked", len(v))

print(step1.bind(step2))
`} />
    </div>

    <!-- 2. Grading on top -->
    <h3>Adding grades on top</h3>
    <p>Now add a grade: T(i, j, e, A) means "start in i, end in j, with effect e, producing A." Composition requires index match (handshake) AND grade composition (budget accounting). This is Definition 3. The paper uses a preordered semiring for grades; here we use (&#x2115;, +, 0): natural numbers with addition.</p>

