    <!-- 3. Restricted pointwise order -->
    <h3>The restricted pointwise order</h3>
    <p>Kura's innovation: the <strong>restricted pointwise order</strong> on graded predicates. A graded predicate Q at grade e refines Q' at grade e' if e ≤ e' and Q(x) implies Q'(x) for all x. This lets you weaken postconditions by increasing the allowed effect budget.</p>

    <svg viewBox="0 0 500 150" class="w-full max-w-md my-4" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
      <!-- Bottom-left: tight Q, low cost (refines) -->
