    <!-- 4. The handshake (Def 7) -->
    <h3>The handshake — Definition 7</h3>
    <p>Definition 7 gives the composition rule for indexed graded Hoare triples. If <code>{'{P}'} c₁ : (i→j, e₁) {'{R}'}</code> and <code>{'{R}'} c₂ : (j→k, e₂) {'{Q}'}</code>, then <code>{'{P}'} c₁;c₂ : (i→k, e₁·e₂) {'{Q}'}</code>. The intermediate R is the handshake: it must satisfy both the postcondition of c₁ and the precondition of c₂, at matching index j.</p>

    <svg viewBox="0 0 500 200" class="w-full max-w-md my-4" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
